         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/6/87 ¶  ¶ I am aware, dear Mr Dyer, that many novelties occur among Mr Forbes Papuan plants, and I hope to work them out during the latter half of this year, when my “Key to the syst. of Vict. plan...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.06.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 224-5.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 8 Aug 1887<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">and annotated by W. Thiselton-Dyer</seg>: Answered 10.8.87<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">[l</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">etter not found]</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>28/6/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am aware, dear Mr Dyer, that many novelties occur among Mr Forbes Papuan plants, and I hope to work them out during the latter half of this year, when my “Key to the syst. of Vict. plants”<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.11.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will be out,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and thus my time be free again for the New Guinea Flora. From Mr Carruthers you will have learnt, that the elaboration of the Dicotyledoneae is left to me (except Euphorbiaceae &amp; Utriceae.) Mr Ridley takes the Monocotyledoneae and Mr Carruthers the ferns.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Carruthers, 1 March 1886; M to H. Ridley, 12 January 1887<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 87-01-12d).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As the R. Austr. geogr. Soc. voted for Forbes last tour on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">my</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>proposition somewhat reluctantly £500 - -, it would be but just that the elaboration of his plants, as far as just indicated, should be left to me. I am too far from Europe, to make further arrangements; moreover such overwhelming material is from other tropic regions in England, to be worked out, that the Papuan Flora, as Sir Joseph Hooker conceded already some years ago, should be left to me, as I was first in the field.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 25 March<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1873; J. Hooker to M, 17 January 1884.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>My strenght and eyesight may last me perhaps only yet a short time, but so long as it does, no one will, I feel sure, grudge me the New Guinea work</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I believe, that I shall be able to congratulate you soon on some honors from Germany.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thiselton-Dyer was elected to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Academia Caesarea Leopoldino-Carolina Naturae Curiosorum in 1887 (List of members,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <ref target="http://www.leopoldina.org/en/members/members-since-1652/">
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0000FF; ">http://www.leopoldina.org/en/members/members-since-1652/</seg>
                        </ref>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>[accessed 6 December 2014]</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If Mr Forbes,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">as I recently have recommended</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>gets means from the special Commissioner Mr Douglas, for further travels in N. Guinea out of the £15 000 voted by N.S.W. Vict. &amp; Queensl., then Mr Forbes will in honor be bound to render his collections accessible to the three colonies, which give him the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>means (and probably the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">only</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>means) for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>continuing his researches.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Forbes; M's recommendation not found.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Commissioner</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>spent £135/10/6 to</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>support<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Forbes's</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>final expedition in New Guinea from 1 October to 7 November 1887, see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">British New Guinea. Report for the year 1887</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, Victoria, Parliamentary paper 1888, no. 32, pp. 29-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">35</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">T</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">he 'principal object [was] to extend the area of geographical discovery' (p. 29)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Forbes' report does not mention<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">collections</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Any unfairness in this respect would likely be made not only a subject of discussions in the colonial press here, but also most likely in the three parliaments; which vote the fund for the High Commissioner.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Todd (1894), pp. 248-53.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dicotyledoneae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Euphorbiaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monocotyledoneae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Utriceae</p>
         </div>
